<!--<h4><hi rend="italic">Romanized text.</hi></h4>-->

<p>Bismi 'llahi 'l-rahmāni 'ḷ-raḥīm</p>

<p>Bāgh6i rāḥat bakh6sh6 gulzāri iram ra toāmān.</p>

<p>Bānīyash6 kh6āni Jahāngīr ast bā tamkīngsh6ān.</p>

<p>Sabzā,sh mīnāwash6s gulhash6 hamcḵon simo zar.</p>

<p>“Bāgh6i minā” cāli tarikh6ash6 kh6irad gufta azan. </p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:KrishnaSastri1925_01">

<hi rend="italic">Translation.</hi>

<p>In the name of God, the merciful and compassionate.</p>

<p>This delightful garden, a twin of the garden of Paradise.</p>

<p>Its founder is the world-conquering (Jahangir) Kh6an, with dignity and majesty.</p>

<p>Its verdure is like enamel' its flowers like silver and gold.</p>

<p>Hence wisdom composed the chronogram: “Enamelled garden.” 1104 A. H. — 1692 A. D.<note n="355-1">I am indebted to Mr. G.Yazdani, M.A., the Government Epigraphist for Moslem inscriptions for text and translation of this inscription.</note></p>

</div>

